subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
(
Fig. 5A
). Head capsule subquadrate; cervical sclerites small. Frontal lines visible only basally; coronal line absent. Surface of head capsule smooth. Six stemmata on each anterolateral corner of head capsule. Clypeolabrum (
Fig. 5B
) strongly asymmetrical. Nasale with median projection bearing ca. five small teeth. Lateral lobes of epistome present on left side but absent on right side; left lobe very strongly projecting anteriorly, lateral margin of left lobe partially membranous; anterior margin of right epistome almost straight or very weakly rounded.
